Pika World Equity Analysis- 13 August 2021Inflation Worry Roars AgainWhile the Wednesday CPI data shows inflation becoming muted  the latest PPI data showed that inflation might be stickier than we thought.The PPI increased by 1% on a month over month basis without any signs of cooling off. As such  Pika World believes that the market will continue to debate whether inflation is truly transitory.Banks Stocks Continue to Shine in Mid-Cycle TransitionWhen the end of August arrives  investors will have a clearer picture if Uncle Powell will move decisively to end the easy monetary policy that has pushed the equity market consistently higher for the past two decades.The Fed’s annual summer gathering at Jackson Hole on 26-28 August will highlight investors hunt for clues. As a result  we expect potential volatility in both stocks and options markets.Most central bankers have indicated their desire to pull back the generous monetary support. Investors are baking in more expectation of such a move becoming a reality. While the annual Fed meeting at Jackson Hole is often a highlight  this year is more critical as S&P 500 sits at record levels  and Covid 19 remains a hanging threat  potentially giving Uncle Powell an uncertainty to handle.Financial Sectors to See TailwindsGiven the backdrop of economic data  Pika World will accumulate further on the rate-sensitive financial sector through exposure in ETFs such as XLF. The counter has risen by about 56% this year  as it pushes our portfolio returns and if interest rate is poised to move higher as expected  then there is some reasonability for XLF to move north further.Even if there is no major announcement in Jackson Hole  we expect that the financial sector will see more focus as investors will increase anticipation that some action will come in the final three meetings of FOMC  such as in September  November and December.What’s on the Menu Today?At 10 pm  we will receive the Michigan Consumer Sentiment  and we expect it to remain unchanged at 81.2.It is 13 August  Friday  8.08 am in Singapore and 8.08 pm in New York. The market is getting more volatile  and we hope all friends have a safe ride on the last trading day!If you find the content in this group useful  share it with your friends through the link:https://t.me/invest_with_pika_world  as it will help us reach out to a broader audience.
